modules.description: Handles PDF page rendering with support for coordinate transformation, text extraction, and image embedding. Operates on PDF documents, pages, and graphical objects such as paths and text blocks. Used to generate vector graphics output, convert text layers to images, and manipulate page layouts programmatically.

The module offers window management, color manipulation, and low-level 2D graphics operations like drawing lines, curves, and shapes using integer coordinates and geometric primitives. It handles graphical contexts, color values, and images to enable tasks such as rendering diagrams, visualizations, or interactive graphics. Specific use cases include creating filled polygons, text annotations, and dynamic graphical interfaces with precise control over positioning and styling.
